main event: Ground observers in Baltimore reported an orange colored object in the sky on 25 October 1953.
interesting points: The object was noted to be slightly larger than a star and first appeared orange before turning white, it had two smaller red lights on either side, both observers reported a length of observation between 5 to 7 minutes, the object traveled from northwest to southeast without any maneuvers before suddenly disappearing, the military indicated it was likely a jet aircraft in the area.
sighted object: an orange colored object with white and red lights
witness description: Ground observers including a PFC and a civilian reported the sighting.
